It's a g]]></description><link>https://www.nadaegyun.com/improving-self-esteem/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Ghost__Post__6061328ed3ebf7001c115124</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Daegyun Na]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 31 Mar 2021 09:26:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Start your favorite activity.<br>Some may say that they don't have an activity they like.<br>But before I say'nothing'<br>If I go back to my past, everyone lives<br>What I did while having fun, the activity that I felt joyful about doing this<br>I think I have one.</br></br></br></br></br></p><p>In my case, I can sing, read a book, play the guitar, talk to me, watch a movie, etc.<br>If possible, rather than end with'watching a movie'<br>How to make it mine after watching a movie<br>By keeping a short diary about watching a movie or'review'<br>It's a good idea to create a story.</br></br></br></br></p><p>It is because such stories gather to create my emotions, my personality, and my story. ^^</p><ol><li>Write down what you like about yourself</li></ol><p>Write 10 things you like about the things that make up you.<br>It can be your appearance, your personality, your ability.<br>It doesn't matter if it's very trivial.<br>'The fingers are long and thin'<br>'I feel good about laughing', etc.</br></br></br></br></p><p>If you think you don’t have anything you like because of your low self-esteem<br>Ask a friend or family member who cares about you.<br>Then write it down instead of'denying' it.<br>If you look at it every day and try to acknowledge your strengths,<br>At some point you'll start to see things that you like.</br></br></br></br></p><ol><li>Keep away or ignore self-esteem vampires</li></ol><p>Self-esteem vampires are people who lower my self-esteem and hurt self-esteem.</p><p>Ordinary people easily say things that hurt<br>They say,'It's all telling you to do well.'<br>No matter how much you think of me, my energy<br>If I can’t accept that, so if it acts as a negative energy for me<br>It can never be a good story.</br></br></br></br></p><p>If even the best gift in the world doesn’t suit the recipient,<br>It's not a great gift, it's just useless.</br></p><p>In the name of family, in the name of friends<br>The people who hurt me are tied to the'relationship' of family or friends<br>If left unattended, you can make yourself more atrophied.</br></br></p><p>I think the story they are telling<br>If it negatively affects me, it's good to take a short distance.<br>It is like minimizing the time to bump into, or having fewer meetings.</br></br></p><p>People who thought they were family,<br>To stay away from close friends who thought there was only one<br>It won't be easy.</br></br></p><p>But if they really are for me<br>I will try to hear my story, why I want to distance them from them.<br>If not, you don't have to be disappointed.</br></br></p><p>When it comes to affecting self-esteem,'relationships' really play a big part.<br>It's because people hurt the most.<br>Here's how to make yourself stronger.</br></br></p><ol><li>Making a person who sees my strengths</li></ol><p>The wounds received as a self-esteem vampire are due to relationships with good people<br>It can be healed. But people with low self-esteem<br>Determining whether this person is really for me because of a wound or a lack<br>It can be difficult.</br></br></br></p><p>So you have to be more careful, but nevertheless<br>If you look around well, you will see my strengths that will hold my hand<br>There are many people who have a positive influence.</br></br></p><p>Yesterday, an impressive article appeared.<br>It was an article titled'Because I'm so hard, but will you hug me only once?'<br>A girl in her school uniform said to the person sitting next to her,<br>Most people hug and comfort students<br>They bought me a drink or something to eat.<br>Watch what you do well<br>If you are looking for someone who motivates you to grow and develop in a good direction<br>I think it will be a good influence on me and my life.</br></br></br></br></br></br></br></p><ol><li>Praise yourself in the mirror once a day</li></ol><p>Do you like to look in the mirror?<br>I don't like it, but I don't like it.</br></p><p>Mirrors are a great tool to positively consciousize your image.<br>Of course, you can also become conscious negatively.</br></p><p>What do you see first in the mirror?<br>The person who sees the complex first, the person who sees the most fleshy part first<br>Please change your gaze and praise your external part.</br></br></p><p>It doesn't look shiny, but it's thick, so it's nice.<br>It’s the right size, so it’s very trivial to wear shoes.<br>It can be an important compliment.</br></br></p><p>Of course, it is also important to recognize the complex as it is.<br>If you have a lot of belly fat, consider it only as a fact that you have'too much belly fat'.<br>After that, don't come to a conclusion like'I'm ugly, I'm fat'. Hahaha</br></br></p><p>Because the brain creates my image by stacking up what I think<br>At some point, even though I wasn't really ugly and fat<br>The moment will come when you recognize yourself that way.</br></br></p><p>Remember, the habit of being positively conscious of yourself increases your self-esteem.</p><ul><li>Leads to 10 ways to restore self-esteem (bottom). ^^ *<br><a href="https://brunch.co.kr/@ansyd/39">https://brunch.co.kr/@ansyd/39</a><br>10 ways to restore self-esteem (bottom)<br>10 ways to restore self-esteem, organized by Style Coach (bottom)</br></br></br></li><li>This is a continuation of the 10 ways to restore self-esteem (top). ^^ *<br><a href="https://brunch.co.kr/@ansyd/38">https://brunch.co.kr/@ansyd/38</a></br></li><li>Getting in the habit of accepting praise</li></ul><p>It’s the sixth time now. This takes a lot of effort.<br>Did you do it with 7 things? ㅎㅎㅎ;;</br></p><p>I've been taught that it is humility to refuse praise.<br>But even rejection is modest.<br>I see that most of the people in our country<br>I couldn't take it well and I couldn't even say'praise' well.</br></br></br></p><p>A society that is stingy with'praise'<br>Sometimes I think I'm proud.<br>But it seems that sometimes it takes skill to accept praise.<br>It really depends on what kind of situation, what kind of target, what kind of context it is.</br></br></br></p><p>Nevertheless, the praise that comes to me<br>'Thank you.' Or, naturally, passing it over as a compliment<br>Habits support self-affirmation.</br></br></p><p>No matter how much you praise, people who cannot accept themselves<br>Expectations of yourself are so great that accepting them<br>It may be unacceptable.<br>'I'm still far away.' The thought of'I'm too shy to be praised like this'<br>It could be because you listened too hard.<br>But when the other person sees it, I want to praise him<br>Rather than refusing that part with my will<br>Wouldn't it be better to accept lightly with'thank you' for positive development? ^^</br></br></br></br></br></br></br></p><ol><li>Learn confident styling/makeup/hair</li></ol><p>This also has to do with what I do.<br>Balance is important in everything.</br></p><p>Decorating your appearance doesn't mean you've been neglected inside.<br>It is important for my self-esteem to take care of the outside with the inside.</br></p><p>Finding the style that suits you, finding makeup,<br>Hair that will make me confident<br>When you look in the mirror, it has the effect that you like yourself more.</br></br></p><p>By finding the image I was hoping for<br>Confidence increases with self-esteem.</br></p><p>However, the important thing is that it must be an external self-esteem accompanied by inner strength.<br>After removing colorful makeup, I feel shabby<br>Anyone who can’t go outside<br>It is enough to take care of your appearance, but lack the attitude of self-recognition.</br></br></br></p><p>Styling, makeup, and hair<br>These are the tools you can use to become the better me, the one you want,<br>It shouldn't be a tool to cover me.<br>By acknowledging myself and putting on the appropriate wrapping paper<br>Don't forget that I can shine more. ^^</br></br></br></br></p><ol><li>Learn to comfort yourself by patting yourself</li></ol><p>Find a friend when you need comfort<br>Consultation</br></p>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bitcoin]]></title><description><![CDATA[daily life]]></description><link>https://www.nadaegyun.com/20210321</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Ghost__Post__6061328ed3ebf7001c115129</guid><category><![CDATA[DAY]]></category><dc:creator><![CDATA[Daegyun Na]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 21 Mar 2021 11:48:00 GMT</pubDate><media:content url="https://www.nadaegyun.com/static/9323620ffa16334e92c8c28cf647bde0/20210321.png" medium="image"/><content:encoded><![CDATA[<blockquote>별다른 새로운 일이 없던 한주였다. 동아리 후배가 새로운 비트코인 몇 종류를 알려주어서 후배와 연락하게 되었고, 관심사가 비슷한 일로 만난 띠동갑과 이런 저런 이야기를 나누었고, 엄마가 아빠에게 잔소리하듯 와이프에게 이것저것 잔소리를 하였다.</blockquote><img src="https://www.nadaegyun.com/static/9323620ffa16334e92c8c28cf647bde0/20210321.png" alt="Bitcoin"/><p>오늘은 어떤 이야기를 남겨야 할까? 키보드를 보자니 인생은 Control, Option, Command와 여러 가지 조합으로 이루어 진듯하다.</p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/03/KakaoTalk_Photo_2021-03-21-10-50-41.jpeg" class="kg-image" alt="Bitcoin"/></figure><p>오랜만에 출근하여 오랫동안 얼굴만 알던 사람과 우연히 사람 관계에 대한 이야기를 하게 되었고 상대의 입장에 따라 사건은 주관적으로 정리가 된다고 다시 한번 느끼게 되었다.</p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/03/tempImage2EizSX.gif" class="kg-image" alt="Bitcoin"/></figure><p>최근 서울과 경기도에 살고 있는 외국인에 대한 코로나 검사가 진행되었다는 것을 인도 동료로부터 회의하면서 듣게 되었다. 갑자기 나는 코로나 검사 결과가 음성인지 물어보는 것이었다. 뭔 소리인가 해서 들어보니 인사과에서 특정일까지 코로나 검사를 받고 결과를 통보하지 않으면 벌금 2천 달러를 내야 한다는 것이었다. 난 외국인 차별이다란 생각으로 뭘로 표현해야 하나 생각하다 "differentiation"이다 말이었지만 그친구는 "racism"이라고 말하였다. </p><p>다름(different)과 틀림(incorrect)은 구분해야 한다던 친구가 생각났다. 나는 의미 전달에 문제가 없다면 문법과 단어에 깊게 고민하지 않는다. 이래서 독일어를 배우지 못하는 것 같다. 언젠가는 수학처럼 답이 딱 떨어지는 학문을 배우는 게 좋았지만, 살면서 느끼는 것은 뭔가 딱 떨어지는 것보다 그냥 의미만 통해도 되는 그런 것들이 피곤하지 않고 뭐 그렇다. 언제는 하루에 "출근한다.", "나왔다" 만 말하고 거의 되지도 않는 영어로 의미만 잘 전달하자란 생각으로 일했던 것 같다. </p><p>같은 말을 사용하는 사람과도 의미 전달이 안되는 세상인데 되지도 않는 영어로 밥 먹고사는 거 보면 나는 정말 대단한 사람인 것 같다. ㅋㅋㅋ</p><p/>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[리더의 자존감 공부]]></title><description><![CDATA[2021년 3월 14일, '리더의 자존감 공부'를 읽었다.  블로그를 쓰다 보니 오늘이 '화이트 데이'라는 것도 알게 되었다. 이제 어느덧 이벤트에 무덤덤한 나이가 된 것일까? 이어폰으로 너튜부에서 김동률의 '취중진담'이 흘러 나온다.]]></description><link>https://www.nadaegyun.com/20210314/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Ghost__Post__6061328ed3ebf7001c115128</guid><category><![CDATA[DAY]]></category><dc:creator><![CDATA[Daegyun Na]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 14 Mar 2021 04:47:00 GMT</pubDate><media:content url="https://www.nadaegyun.com/static/36e0819ad47b55f51325289eca71892a/tempImagesHPC7P.gif" medium="image"/><content:encoded><![CDATA[<blockquote>2021년 3월 14일, '리더의 자존감 공부'를 읽었다.  블로그를 쓰다 보니 오늘이 '화이트 데이'라는 것도 알게 되었다. 이제 어느덧 이벤트에 무덤덤한 나이가 된 것일까? 이어폰으로 너튜부에서 김동률의 '취중진담'이 흘러 나온다.</blockquote><img src="https://www.nadaegyun.com/static/36e0819ad47b55f51325289eca71892a/tempImagesHPC7P.gif" alt="리더의 자존감 공부"/><p> 일요일 오전에는 와이프와 아들이 바이올린과 첼로를 배운다. 2015년인가 시작은 같이 했었는데 나의 게으름으로 인하여 나는 포기하고 둘은 포기하지 않고 교회 다니듯이 일요일 오전에 아직 배우고 있다. 농담 삼아 때가 되면 길거리 연주를 시키며 그 동안 투자한 레슨비를 벌겠다 했는데 실력이 그 정도는 아닌듯 하다. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/03/tempImageQ7VGnb.gif" class="kg-image" alt="리더의 자존감 공부"/></figure><p> 나는 일요일 아침 이 시간이 좋다. 내가 좋아하는 얼 그레이 향에 취해 이 넓은 카페를 혼자 독차지 하고, 혼자 만의 시간을 즐기는 이 시간이 이 느낌이 좋다.</p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/03/tempImageif5qfT.gif" class="kg-image" alt="리더의 자존감 공부"/></figure><p> 열정을 잃어 버린 지 벌써 4년이 지났고, 열정을 잃어버리니 개구쟁이 마음도 잃어 버렸다. 안 좋았던 기억은 시간이 지나면 마음에서 잊혀져야 하는데 후회 아닌 미련으로 남아 자꾸 돌아보게 된다. </p><p> 나의 혼자만의 시간이 끝나려 한다. 어여 독후감을 써야겠다. 다른 사람을 비난 한다는 것! 일종의 자기 방어인가 싶다. 타인을 있는 그대로 