26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDQzfHxhcyUyMHRoZXklMjBhcmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjE1NTM5MjE5&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=1000 1000w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1532553458865-bd0d17a60348?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDQzfHxhcyUyMHRoZXklMjBhcmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjE1NTM5MjE5&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=1600 1600w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1532553458865-bd0d17a60348?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDQzfHxhcyUyMHRoZXklMjBhcmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjE1NTM5MjE5&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=2400 2400w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption>Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@will_myers?utm_source=ghost&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=api-credit">Will Myers</a> / <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=api-credit">Unsplash</a></figcaption></img></figure><blockquote>The method is simple. You just have to acknowledge your child's feelings.</blockquote><p> Recognizing emotions is the first step in a concrete practice way of'acknowledging a child as it is. It is easy for parents to stand in their position now and see and judge their child's emotions. It takes practice and effort to consciously look at the child's emotions from the child's point of view in order to recognize <em>'Oh, you are now doing something'</em>.</p><p> Dad puts honey in warm water for the child and handed the cup of honey to the child because he wanted it to be cool enough to eat. The child opened his mouth a little and yelled that it was hot. Dad once again took honey water and said, "What is hot? It is all cold! Now, nothing really is hot", and he gave the cup of honey again to the child. He looked at it again carefully and screamed "It's hot and I wanted to drink it, but it's too hot to drink. I am angry and annoyed."</p><h3 id="you-just-have-to-admit-your-child">You just have to admit your child</h3><p> Everyone wants to be recognized. The small size of a child does not mean that the amount of emotion the child feels is also small.</p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507149214576-19e2f76d09ad?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDF8fGFkbWl0fGVufDB8fHx8MTYxNTUzOTI0MQ&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=2000" class="kg-image" alt="Improving self-esteem in child" srcset="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507149214576-19e2f76d09ad?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDF8fGFkbWl0fGVufDB8fHx8MTYxNTUzOTI0MQ&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=600 600w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507149214576-19e2f76d09ad?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDF8fGFkbWl0fGVufDB8fHx8MTYxNTUzOTI0MQ&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=1000 1000w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507149214576-19e2f76d09ad?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDF8fGFkbWl0fGVufDB8fHx8MTYxNTUzOTI0MQ&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=1600 1600w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507149214576-19e2f76d09ad?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDF8fGFkbWl0fGVufDB8fHx8MTYxNTUzOTI0MQ&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=2400 2400w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption>Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@ryancp?utm_source=ghost&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=api-credit">Ryan Plomp</a> / <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=api-credit">Unsplash</a></figcaption></img></figure><blockquote>"Oh, it's hot? Dad looked like it was cool, but it's still hot for you" "Dad will cool it down quickly~ Hoho, hoohoo~" If you cry while crying?"It takes time to cool down, and crying doesn't cool down quickly~" The child doesn't stop with this healing. It only shows a more grumpy reaction. Even in such a case, let's admit it. "I want to try it quickly, but it's hot so it's hot right away. Isn't it hard to wait until you can't eat and cool more?"</blockquote><p> There is another advantage to acknowledging your child's feelings like this.<br>That is, parents consume less energy. Don't run out of energy by saying,'Is you right, am I right?' This makes it easier for the child to calm down, and the parent can move on to the next step.<br/></br></p><p>What parents want to say must be done after acknowledging the child’s heart first. It is well communicated to the child and is heard by the child. Open your child's ears so they can hear you, and then tell them what you want to say. <em>"It takes time to cool down, what should we wait while our honey water cools down?"</em>  The warm finishes that the honey water was cool enough and ate deliciously while this conversation came and went </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card kg-card-hascaption"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1615477756878-c39a55a0c40f?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8YWxsfDM0fHx8fHx8Mnx8MTYxNTUzOTI5Nw&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=2000" class="kg-image" alt="Improving self-esteem in child" srcset="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1615477756878-c39a55a0c40f?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8YWxsfDM0fHx8fHx8Mnx8MTYxNTUzOTI5Nw&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=600 600w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1615477756878-c39a55a0c40f?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8YWxsfDM0fHx8fHx8Mnx8MTYxNTUzOTI5Nw&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=1000 1000w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1615477756878-c39a55a0c40f?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8YWxsfDM0fHx8fHx8Mnx8MTYxNTUzOTI5Nw&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=1600 1600w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1615477756878-c39a55a0c40f?crop=entropy&#x26;cs=tinysrgb&#x26;fit=max&#x26;fm=jpg&#x26;ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8YWxsfDM0fHx8fHx8Mnx8MTYxNTUzOTI5Nw&#x26;ixlib=rb-1.2.1&#x26;q=80&#x26;w=2400 2400w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"><figcaption>Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@glencarrie?utm_source=ghost&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=api-credit">Glen Carrie</a> / <a href="https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&#x26;utm_medium=referral&#x26;utm_campaign=api-credit">Unsplash</a></figcaption></img></figure><p> Recognizing the child's emotions as they are is the first step in a concrete practice method that acknowledges the child's existence as it is. Recognizing and responding to your child's emotions allows them to perceive their emotions and learn how to respond appropriately when feelings are felt.</p><blockquote> Everyone wants to be recognized, and a child's small size doesn't mean that the child's emotions are small.</blockquote><p/>]]></content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[How to improve self-esteem]]></title><description><![CDATA[People should know how to improve self-esteem and this post will provides you with more information on some actions that you can take to improve it.]]></description><link>https://www.nadaegyun.com/how-to-improve-self-esteem/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Ghost__Post__6061328ed3ebf7001c115120</guid><category><![CDATA[Self-esteem]]></category><dc:creator><![CDATA[Daegyun Na]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 01 Mar 2021 10:50:00 GMT</pubDate><media:content url="https://www.nadaegyun.com/static/43b8f1d6d0cd46c1e13f50d877608af3/photo-1465343161283-c1959138ddaa.jpg" medium="image"/><content:encoded><![CDATA[<blockquote>Self-esteem is how you feel about yourself and everyone has times to feel low, which can lead to problems including mental health such as depression or anxiety.</blockquote><img src="https://www.nadaegyun.com/static/43b8f